An airport database management system (DBMS) is designed to efficiently handle, organize, and retrieve information relevant to airport operations. 
This can include a variety of data such as flight schedules, passenger information, baggage handling, aircraft maintenance, crew schedules, and security protocols.

Components of Airport Database Management System

Flight Schedules: Arrival and departure times, delays, cancellations, and gate assignments.
Flight Status: Real-time updates on the status of flights, including boarding, takeoff, landing, and taxiing.
Passenger Records: Personal details, travel history, frequent flyer information, and special requirements.
Airports: Location,Airport Names,Airlines.
Employee Details

Queries to find insights from the database.
